---
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site.config';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Delete Account & Data - DhanRakshak"
  description="How to delete your DhanRakshak account and all associated data. Complete control over your information."
>
  <Header />
  
  <main class="min-h-screen pt-16 pb-20">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="page-header-banner">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14 md:py-20">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-3">
          <div class="w-11 h-11 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center text-accent">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M14.74 9l-.346 9m-4.788 0L9.26 9m9.968-3.21c.342.052.682.107 1.022.166m-1.022-.165L18.16 19.673a2.25 2.25 0 01-2.244 2.077H8.084a2.25 2.25 0 01-2.244-2.077L4.772 5.79m14.456 0a48.108 48.108 0 00-3.478-.397m-12 .562c.34-.059.68-.114 1.022-.165m0 0a48.11 48.11 0 013.478-.397m7.5 0v-.916c0-1.18-.91-2.164-2.09-2.201a51.964 51.964 0 00-3.32 0c-1.18.037-2.09 1.022-2.09 2.201v.916m7.5 0a48.667 48.667 0 00-7.5 0"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold page-header-title">Delete Account & Data</h1>
            <p class="text-sm page-header-subtitle mt-1">Complete control over your information</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Content -->
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-10 prose-themed">
      <p>DhanRakshak is built with a <strong>privacy-first, local-first</strong> approach. You are always in full control of your data. This page explains how to delete your account, your data, or both.</p>

      <h2>What Data Does DhanRakshak Store?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Local data (on your device):</strong> Expenses, budgets, savings goals, categories, and preferences — stored in the app's local database.</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud data (optional):</strong> If you enabled Cloud Sync, an encrypted backup of your data is stored securely in the cloud.</li>
        <li><strong>Account information:</strong> If you signed in with Google, your display name and email are used for authentication only.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How to Delete Your Local Data</h2>
      <p>You can delete all locally stored data directly from the app:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open <strong>DhanRakshak</strong> on your device.</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> (tap the gear icon on the Profile screen).</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Data Management</strong>.</li>
        <li>Select <strong>Delete Everything</strong> to remove all expenses, budgets, savings goals, and categories.</li>
        <li>Confirm the deletion when prompted.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>You can also delete specific data types individually (expenses only, savings goals only, etc.) from the same Data Management screen.</p>

      <h2>How to Delete Your Cloud Data</h2>
      <p>If you enabled Cloud Sync and want to remove your cloud backup:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Open <strong>DhanRakshak</strong> on your device.</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Cloud Sync</strong>.</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Delete Cloud Data</strong> under Advanced Options.</li>
        <li>Confirm the deletion. This removes all cloud-stored data while keeping your local data intact.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>
      <p>DhanRakshak uses <strong>Google Sign-In</strong> for authentication. To fully remove your account:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Delete your local data</strong> following the steps above.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete your cloud data</strong> if Cloud Sync was enabled.</li>
        <li><strong>Sign out</strong> from the app (Profile screen &gt; Sign Out).</li>
        <li><strong>Uninstall</strong> the app from your device.</li>
        <li>Optionally, revoke DhanRakshak's access from your Google account at <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Account Permissions</a>.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Once these steps are completed, no data associated with your account remains — either on your device or in the cloud.</p>

      <h2>What Gets Deleted</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data type</th>
            <th>Deletion method</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Expenses & transactions</td>
            <td>Settings &gt; Data Management &gt; Delete Everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Budgets</td>
            <td>Settings &gt; Data Management &gt; Delete Everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Savings goals</td>
            <td>Settings &gt; Data Management &gt; Delete Everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Categories & preferences</td>
            <td>Settings &gt; Data Management &gt; Delete Everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cloud backup</td>
            <td>Settings &gt; Cloud Sync &gt; Delete Cloud Data</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Google Sign-In access</td>
            <td><a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Account Permissions</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>DhanRakshak does <strong>not</strong> retain any of your data after deletion. Once deleted:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Local data is permanently removed from your device's database.</li>
        <li>Cloud data is permanently removed from the cloud storage.</li>
        <li>No copies, backups, or logs of your financial data are kept.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Need Help?</h2>
      <p>If you have trouble deleting your data or need assistance, contact us:</p>
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.supportEmail}?subject=Account%20%26%20Data%20Deletion%20Request`}>{siteConfig.supportEmail}</a></p>
      <p><strong>GitHub Issues:</strong> <a href={siteConfig.githubIssuesUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">{siteConfig.githubIssuesUrl}</a></p>
      <p>We will respond to deletion requests within <strong>3 business days</strong>.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
